Package cryptotrader.authentication

Class Database

  • java.lang.Object
    • cryptotrader.authentication.Database
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AddToDatabase, DatabaseAuthenticate, GetFromDatabase
    public class Database
extends Object
implements DatabaseAuthenticate, GetFromDatabase, AddToDatabase
    A class that connects to and performs queries on the project database. Implements the singleton pattern as only one database should be active at any time.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Oscar Yu, David Tran

      • authenticate

        public boolean authenticate​(String username,
                            String password)
        Returns a boolean value specifying the success or failure of a login attempt. The username provided is used to perform a password lookup in the user credential database. If the provided password matches the lookup, the method will return true.
        Specified by:
        authenticate in interface DatabaseAuthenticate
        Parameters:
        username - a string containing the username of the user attempting login
        password - a string containing the password of the user attempting login
        Returns:
        boolean success or failure of authentication (true/false)
